[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926853&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926853&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I evidently wasn't clear enough - some people think I am asking to
allow host names to begin with a digit.  I am not: 3Com.COM is (a)
not a host name, it's a domain name, and (b) is not on the Internet,
so nobody is going to be telnetting or ftping or smtping to them.

What I'm asking is if we change the spec so that domain names (*not*
host names) can begin with a digit, is there code out there which is
up to current spec (e.g. supports MX) that will break?  Putting it
another way, if your mail system handles MX properly, will it break if
you send mail to postmaster@3Com.COM ?

I should also mention that the IN-ADDR domain permits subdomains which
are full digit strings, and that doesn't seem to break anything.

	Mark

